            <header class="mb-10">
                <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-5 leading-tight">The 20 Best Selling Vinyl Records of 2025</h1>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
                    <span>By findyl</span>
                    <span>·</span>
                    <time datetime="2026-02-17">17 February 2026</time>
                    <span>·</span>
                    <span>5 min read</span>
                </div>
            </header>

            <div class="article-body">
                <p>UK vinyl sales hit 7.6 million units in 2025 — the 18th consecutive year of growth for the format. It was a year defined by huge new releases, blockbuster reissues, and the unstoppable force of Taylor Swift, who claimed the top spot for a fourth year running. Here are the 20 best selling vinyl albums of the year, based on Official Charts Company data.</p>
            </div>

            <div id="recordList" class="mt-8 mb-10"></div>

            <div class="article-body">
                <h2>What does this tell us?</h2>
                <p>A few things stand out. Taylor Swift's dominance is now undeniable — four consecutive years at the top of the vinyl chart, and The Life of a Showgirl shifted 126,000 copies in its first week alone, the fastest-selling vinyl album this century. Sam Fender's People Watching is the feel-good story of the year for British music, breaking the record for the biggest opening week by a British artist on vinyl.</p>
                <p>Oasis were everywhere, occupying three slots in the top 20 off the back of their reunion tour and a wave of anniversary reissues. And Rumours by Fleetwood Mac remains one of the most enduring records in history — this is its ninth consecutive year in the UK vinyl year-end top 10.</p>
                <p>The presence of Pulp, Wolf Alice, Wet Leg and Fontaines D.C. is encouraging for anyone who cares about independent-minded British music having a place in the mainstream. 2025 was a good year for vinyl.</p>
            </div>

